DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Upper Limit of Normal 1 Decimal Place Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 1 decimal place numeric value representing the upper level of the normal range of values for any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.
